Should Schools Provide Free Pads and Tampons?

Have you ever experienced period shaming, or â€œperiod poverty"? Should schools step in to help? Should schools be required to provide free pads and tampons to students? How are pads and tampons similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools? How are they different?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe that, under the right circumstances, both pads and tampons are necessary products for women, and that they should be provided for free

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: to provide a private and safe place for girls that are experiencing what some may call humiliating situations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This way the girls won't even have to worry about it, they can just go and get what they need, and leave.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: toilet paper, soap, band aids, etc.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: by the government for a reason, which is to help people that are in need and can't afford those products.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Help make the schools a safer place for the girls.
